      "label": "The System"
    },
    {
      "id": "pol-opposite-group",
      "type": "group",
      "x": -2560,
      "y": 6260,
      "width": 600,
      "height": 540,
      "label": "The Opposite"
    },
    {
      "id": "pol-6ca80daaebefbead",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## From Ethics to Politics: The Bridge\n\nMan as an end in himself is an ethical principle (see Ethics). Its political significance: an individual living alone needs only ethics \u2014 but among other men, he needs a principle that *protects* his moral sovereignty in a social context.\n\nEthics says: each man ought to live by his own rational judgment. But in society, other men can negate that judgment by force. The question becomes: what social conditions does man's nature require? The answer is the concept that provides \"the logical transition from the principles guiding an individual's actions to the principles guiding his relationship with others\" \u2014 *individual rights.*\n\nThis is why politics is a branch of ethics, not an independent discipline. Every political principle \u2014 rights, government, capitalism \u2014 is derived from the ethical fact that man is an end in himself and must be free to act on his own judgment.\n\n*From: Man as an End in Himself [ethics], Rational Self-Interest [ethics]*",
      "x": -2520,
      "y": 3340,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 300
    },
    {
      "id": "pol-880f7d490ef248b1",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Individual Rights\n\n\"Rights are a moral concept \u2014 the concept that provides a logical transition from the principles guiding an individual's actions to the principles guiding his relationship with others \u2014 the concept that preserves and protects individual morality in a social context.\" \u2014 Rand\n\n**The hierarchy of rights:**\n- **Right to Life** (fundamental) \u2014 the source of all rights\n- **Right to Liberty** \u2014 freedom to act on one's own judgment\n- **Right to Property** \u2014 the right to the product of one's effort\n- **Right to the Pursuit of Happiness** \u2014 the right to live for one's own sake\n\nRights are *negative*: freedom FROM coercion, not claims ON others' effort. There are no \"rights\" to the labor of other men. Rights are *absolute*: they cannot be morally infringed for any reason \u2014 not \"the public good,\" not majority vote, not \"social justice.\" Rights are *inalienable*: even when violated by criminals, the right remains on the side of the victim.\n\n**Rand's crucial discovery:** rights can be violated by one means only \u2014 the initiation of physical force (including indirect forms such as fraud).\n\n*From: Man as End in Himself [ethics], Justice [ethics], Right to Property [ethics]*",
      "x": -2520,
      "y": 3820,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 480,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "pol-a828fe67117c2eeb",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## The Non-Initiation of Force Principle\n\n\"The rights of man can be violated by one means only: by the initiation of physical force. One cannot expropriate a man's values, or prevent him from pursuing values, or enslave him in any manner at all, except by the use of physical force.\" \u2014 Peikoff\n\nForce is the *only* action that negates the victim's mind \u2014 the only act that literally stops human self-preservation. Since reason is man's means of survival, and force prevents a man from acting on reason, the initiation of force is the fundamental anti-life act in a social context.\n\nOnly *retaliatory* force \u2014 used in response to initiation \u2014 is moral. The right of self-defense is the corollary of the right to life. All human relationships must be voluntary: persuasion, trade, agreement \u2014 never compulsion.\n\nThis is the ethical principle (force as evil) translated into the political principle: government exists to ban initiation and to place retaliatory force under objective control.\n\n*From: Individual Rights + Initiation of Force as Evil [ethics]*",
      "x": -2820,
      "y": 4480,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 400,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "pol-30d862a9102eed63",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## The Trader Principle\n\nValue for value. Voluntary exchange to mutual benefit. No sacrifice of self to others; no sacrifice of others to self. The trader principle is the only rational form of human interaction \u2014 men deal with one another by exchanging value for value, by mutual consent.\n\nThe ethical root is rational self-interest: a rational man does not seek the unearned, neither in matter nor in spirit. He does not sacrifice his values to others or demand that others sacrifice to him. He trades \u2014 creating value and exchanging it freely.\n\nUnder capitalism, the trader principle becomes the economic principle: the free market is the trader principle writ large \u2014 voluntary exchange of goods, services, and ideas without government interference. Capitalism is the system that makes the trader principle possible by banning the only alternative to trade: physical force.\n\n*From: Individual Rights + Rational Self-Interest [ethics] + Harmony of Interests [ethics]*",
      "x": -2220,
      "y": 4480,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 400,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "pol-b8340f2fd36c0ef6",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Limited Government\n\n\"A government is an institution that holds the exclusive power to enforce certain rules of social conduct in a given geographical area.\" \u2014 Rand\n\nIn a proper society, the government is the *servant* of the citizens, not their ruler. It is the agent of man's self-defense \u2014 and an agent may not initiate force against the innocent. Government has a single delegated power: to use force in *retaliation only*, against those who start its use.\n\n**Three and only three functions:**\n1. **The police** \u2014 to protect men from criminals\n2. **The armed services** \u2014 to protect men from foreign invaders\n3. **The law courts** \u2014 to settle disputes according to objective laws\n\nAny additional function requires the government to *initiate* force against innocent citizens \u2014 at which point it becomes a criminal, not a protector. \"Government is inherently negative. The power of force is the power of destruction, not of creation, and it must be used accordingly \u2014 only to destroy destruction.\"\n\nBy its nature, government holds a monopoly on the use of force. Citizens delegate their right of self-defense to prevent gang warfare and mob rule.\n\n*From: Individual Rights + Non-Initiation of Force*",
      "x": -2820,
      "y": 5060,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 460,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "pol-objective-law",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Objective Law\n\n\"A government is the means of placing the retaliatory use of physical force under *objective control* \u2014 i.e., under objectively defined laws.\" \u2014 Peikoff\n\nA proper government is a \"government of laws, not of men.\" Objective law has two essential features:\n\n**1. Objective validation:** Laws must be rationally grounded in the protection of individual rights. The only system of laws that excludes every element of the nonobjective is one that confines legislation to the protection of rights.\n\n**2. Objective interpretation:** Rational laws prohibit only crimes defined in terms of *specific physical acts*. A citizen can know, before acting, whether the law forbids it \u2014 the meaning is grasped from the statement of the law itself. This stands in stark contrast to nonobjective laws forbidding \"blasphemy,\" \"obscenity,\" \"unfair profits,\" or \"restraint of trade\" \u2014 where men must guess at the legislator's intentions.\n\n**Nonobjective law** is the negation of government's purpose: \"a monopoly on the use of force granted to an agency ruled by whim \u2014 a government of men and not of laws \u2014 a formal authorization for the state to swallow up the citizens.\"\n\n*From: Limited Government \u2014 government acts under objective control*",
      "x": -2220,
      "y": 5060,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 460,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "pol-84c75b9c48f22a02",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Laissez-Faire Capitalism\n\n\"Capitalism is a social system based on the recognition of individual rights, including property rights, in which all property is privately owned.\" \u2014 Rand\n\nUnder capitalism, state and economics are separated just as state and church are \u2014 and for the same reason: the mind requires freedom. Producers obey the criminal law and abide by court decisions, but otherwise the government's policy is: *hands off.*\n\n**The only moral social system.** \"Since rights are the means of subordinating society to moral law, capitalism is the only moral social system.\" It is the only system that bans force from human relationships and makes the achievement of virtue possible.\n\n**The system of objectivity.** \"Capitalism implements the right code of morality because it is based on the right view of metaphysics and epistemology. It is the system of virtue because it is the system of objectivity.\" Capitalism protects objective rights by means of objective laws \u2014 allowing cause and effect to operate unimpeded.\n\nWhat capitalism guarantees is that if a man chooses to think, he *can* act accordingly. No one has the power to neutralize the mind.\n\n*From: Individual Rights + Trader Principle + Non-Initiation of Force + Limited Government + Objective Law*",
      "x": -2520,
      "y": 5700,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 420,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "pol-statism",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Statism: The Politics of Unreason\n\n\"Statism\" means any system that concentrates power in the state at the expense of individual freedom. It subsumes theocracy, absolute monarchy, Nazism, fascism, communism, democratic socialism, and dictatorship. The variants differ on form, tactics, and ideology \u2014 but the essence is the same: \"war against man \u2014 against his mind, body, and property alike.\"\n\n**\"Just as individualism is the politics demanded by reason, so statism is the politics of unreason.\"** A free system flows from a philosophy that accepts reality, reason, egoism, and productiveness. An unfree system flows from and fosters the opposite.\n\n**Anarchism** is not the opposite of statism \u2014 it is a variant of it. \"The only referent of 'anarchism' \u2014 the only possible political system it designates \u2014 is some variant of statism.\" Without government, men resort to gang warfare; the result is the negation, not the extreme, of freedom.\n\n**The mixed economy** is \"not a 'third way' between capitalism and socialism. It is merely a transition stage, a disintegrating antisystem, careening drunkenly but inexorably from freedom to dictatorship.\" It rests on pragmatism and eclecticism \u2014 the attempt to combine essentials from contradictory approaches.\n\n*Negated by: Individual Rights, Objective Law, Laissez-Faire Capitalism*",
      "x": -2520,
      "y": 6300,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 460,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "pol-money-group",
      "type": "group",
      "x": -1760,
      "y": 4440,
      "width": 620,
      "height": 1260,
      "label": "Money & Banking"
    },
    {
      "id": "pol-gender-group",
      "type": "group",
      "x": -1760,
      "y": 3200,
      "width": 620,
      "height": 1140,
      "label": "Gender & Romance"
    },
    {
      "id": "pol-money-property",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Money & Property\n\n\"Property is a set of legal rights.\" Property is not the thing \u2014 it is a legal claim on the use of state force to exclude others from controlling that in which you hold property. Land is not property; you hold *property in* land.\n\n**Money** is any form of property that reliably can be exchanged for other property or labor. The key qualifier is *reliability* of acceptance. \"Once everyone believes that a certain kind of property will be accepted by others, it's money.\"\n\nIn modern economies, two kinds of money exist:\n1. **Currency** \u2014 central bank notes and coins\n2. **Credit** \u2014 bank IOUs (your bank balance is the bank's promise to pay you in currency)\n\nA bank loan is not a transfer of cash \u2014 it is a **trade of debts**: you trade your untrusted IOU for the bank's trusted IOU. Interest is the price of renting the bank's credibility.\n\n\"Money is force, if you want to put it that way. All property is force. And in civilized worlds, we trade force for force.\"\n\n*From: Right to Property [ethics] + Trader Principle*\n*Source: McKeever, Understanding Money & Banking Pts. 1-2*",
      "x": -1720,
      "y": 4480,
      "width": 540,
      "height": 500,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "pol-sound-money",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Sound Money vs. Fiat Currency\n\nIncreasing the money supply does not create wealth \u2014 it merely cuts the same pie into smaller slices. \"You do not increase the wealth of society by changing the number of dollars. All that can change the wealth of society is productivity.\"\n\n**Counterfeiting is theft** \u2014 not because the counterfeiter gained without working, but because he *transferred* purchasing power from every dollar-holder to himself. Even when inflation matches economic growth and prices remain stable, the counterfeiter captures 100% of the productivity gains that should have accrued to savers. \"He steals from you covertly... and you're powerless to catch him.\"\n\n**Legal tender laws** transform currency into a tool of expropriation. \"Legal tender laws give every man the right to expropriate his fellow man.\" Acceptance under legal tender is not genuine consent.\n\n**Fractional reserve banking** is morally identical to counterfeiting: both inflate the money supply and transfer wealth without consent. The productive-use defense fails \u2014 the saver could have made the same productive loan himself. Rand's philosophy entails **100% reserve banking**: banks can only lend money actually on deposit. Gold's monetary virtue is practical (hard to inflate), not metaphysical.\n\n*From: Right to Property + Non-Initiation of Force \u2192 inflation as initiation of force*\n*Source: McKeever, Understanding Money & Banking Pts. 3-6 + Fractional Reserve Banking vs. Rand's Ethics*",
      "x": -1720,
      "y": 5040,
      "width": 540,
      "height": 620,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "pol-masc-fem-nature",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Masculine & Feminine Nature\n\nMen and women are fundamentally different \u2014 a metaphysical/biological fact, not a social construct. **Men are producers; women are consumers.** The productive gap is not explained by physical weakness or cognitive deficiency \u2014 women retain the basic capacity to reason. \"It is only the willingness to think that distinguishes a genius from an ordinary mind.\" The deepest reason for women's inferior productivity is that **women lack ambition.**\n\n**Femininity is the stylization of consumption.** \"Women are self-painted works of art, and their theme is pleasure.\" When a woman paints her nails, she treats a universal symbol of labor as another opportunity to decorate \u2014 stressing her role as consumer. As passengers in life, women become mesmerized by the beauty of passing scenery in a way that men, as drivers, cannot.\n\nMasculinity and femininity are not social constructs \u2014 \"acting like a man is acting according to your actual biological metaphysical nature\" (Tew). Gender egalitarianism is **sex nihilism**: the obliteration of real distinctions. Transgender ideology represents the **primacy of consciousness** \u2014 reshaping physical reality to match subjective psychology.\n\n*From: Primacy of Existence [metaphysics] \u2192 man's nature includes biological sex*\n*Sources: Substack article; Tew \u2014 MGTOW (QhOpkwqTFoo), Gender Fluidity (QqbeyJ0ytT4)*",
      "x": -1720,
      "y": 3240,
      "width": 540,
      "height": 500,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "pol-romance-strength",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Romance & the Sexual Asymmetry\n\n**Sex is an act of super-production.** By manufacturing joy itself \u2014 hers and, as a result, his own \u2014 a man goes beyond the problem of *how* to survive to solve the problem of *why* to survive. The form of joy a man experiences is **happiness**: a sense of metaphysical competence rooted in the knowledge that existence is intelligible to reason. Women experience a derivative exaltation \u2014 pleasure, not happiness.\n\n**Men and women are perfect complements, with an asymmetry.** A driver cannot have a passenger until he has learned to drive; a passenger can be driven without knowing anything. Men cannot be romantic before being productive \u2014 they are romantic *by providing*. **For men, romance cannot be primary \u2014 for women, it must be.** Men are independent; women live in accordance with their nature only in the context of romantic relationship with a man.\n\nProviding for another is better than providing for oneself \u2014 there is greater pleasure in an external perspective on the enjoyment one's work has made possible. \"A woman's purpose is to objectify a man's success by enjoying it.\"\n\n\"Romance is the shoring up of the female deficit of strength with the male surplus\" (Tew). Life is about two things: career and romance. The **egalitarian pivot** destroys this complementarity by demanding men and women be treated as \"the same.\"\n\n*From: Masculine & Feminine Nature + Rational Self-Interest [ethics]*\n*Sources: Substack article; Tew \u2014 MGTOW (QhOpkwqTFoo), Shane (5M0W7GLjHK4)*",
      "x": -1720,
      "y": 3800,
      "width": 540,
      "height": 580,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
